s, and discuss recipients’ characteristics and the types of benefits they receive. This is an invaluable reference for researchers and policy makers that features detailed analyses of many of the most important transfer programs in the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEconomic securityzUnited StatesxTesting. 0aEconomic securityzUnited States. 0aIncome maintenance programszUnited States. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh  agovernment policy.  apoverty.  aprogram evaluation.  atransfer programs.  awelfare.1 aBuchmueller, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHam, John C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoynes, Hilary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoffitt, Robert A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoffitt, Robert A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNichols, Austin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRothstein, Jesse, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchanzenbach, Diane Whitmore, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShore-Sheppard, Lara D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZiliak, James P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831107109840 cprintz978022637047740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226370507423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226370507/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles